# API routes

Route handlers live in `app/api/**/route.ts`. Keep them thin: create the stream/response, delegate to `lib/`. Validate inputs in `lib/` or route as appropriate; return meaningful HTTP status codes.

## Thin route pattern

Streaming routes (`describe`, `comfyui/process`) only wire `ReadableStream` + headers:

- `app/api/describe/route.ts` → `lib/describe-route.ts` (`runDescribeStream`)
- `app/api/comfyui/process/route.ts` → `lib/comfyui-process-route.ts` (`runComfyUIProcessStream`)

Add business logic in `lib/`, not in `route.ts`.

## Streaming

- Use `ReadableStream` for SSE (`text/event-stream`).
- Helpers: `lib/streaming.ts` — `sendStreamMessage`, `sendStreamError`, `closeStream`, `readFetchSSEStream`.
- Close streams on error; log server-side; do not expose secrets.
- ComfyUI process: shared subscription in `lib/comfyui-process-stream.ts` — unsubscribing must not abort the job.

## Describe (`/api/describe`)

- Handler: `lib/describe-route.ts`
- Ollama vision stream; art-critic user prompt from `buildDescribePrompt()` in `lib/describe-route.ts` (prose + tags, not JSON config)
- No custom Ollama modelfile — default model is `llava:7b` from `config/models.json`
- Cap length via `lib/prompt-limits.ts`
- Best-effort ComfyUI `/free` before Ollama to release GPU on Apple Silicon

## Process (`/api/comfyui/process`)

- Handler: `lib/comfyui-process-route.ts`
- Auto-start ComfyUI via `lib/comfyui-startup.ts` if needed
- Workflows: `lib/comfyui-workflow.ts` (Flux), `lib/comfyui-workflow-sd.ts` (SD)
- Progress: `lib/comfyui-poll.ts` (WS + HTTP fallback); phased UI via `lib/processing-progress.ts`
- Emit `meta` with `promptId` + `jobStartTime` for client recovery via `/api/comfyui/process/result`

## Outputs / archive

- Listing and delete: `lib/output-archive.ts`
- Serve archive images from `/api/outputs/image/[filename]` with cache-busting (`?v=mtime`), not raw filesystem paths
- Delete generated: `?kind=generated&filename=…`; delete upload: `?kind=upload&imageId=…`
